        <comment xml:lang="en">Hydrazine sulfate is used in the metal industry (refining rare metals,  in analyses performed on minerals and slag, estimating the arsenic content in metals and other)(NTP, 2016). Additionally, it is used in medicine and medical tests, in the production of chemicals (hydrazine hydrate and others, in condensation reactions, as a catalyst in making acetate fibers), as a fungicide and germicide (NTP, 2016). 

Reference(s):  NTP (National Toxicology Program). 2016. Report on Carcinogens, Fourteenth Edition.; Research Triangle Park, NC: U.S. Department of Health and Human Services, Public Health Service. http://ntp.niehs.nih.gov/go/roc14/, accessed 1 March 2017
</comment>
